  digest: fBUJgwJw8c1XGxL1ez4FoeFKG01Qid4SiolVByZ0DJw
review:
  thoroughness: high
  understanding: high
  rating: strong
comment: |-
  Widely used base64 encode/decode crate by Marshall Pierce. Read every
  .rs file under src/ (alphabet, encode, decode, engine/general_purpose
  mod+decode+decode_suffix, engine/mod, engine/naive [test-only],
  chunked_encoder, display, read/decoder, write/encoder+string_writer,
  prelude, lib).
  
  Supply chain (concern #1):
  - No build.rs, no proc-macro, no production dependencies (alloc/std
    feature gates only). Dev-deps only: clap, criterion, once_cell, rand,
    rstest, rstest_reuse, strum.
  - License MIT OR Apache-2.0, repo
    github.com/marshallpierce/rust-base64, well-established author.
  - No process/network/fs/libc usage; grep for std::process, std::net,
    std::fs, libc, include_bytes!, extern "C" found nothing.
  
  unsafe (concerns #2/#3):
  - `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]` at src/lib.rs:233. No unsafe anywhere in
    the crate, so SAFETY-comment and miri caps do not apply. Two
    `unsafe` mentions in source are in comments only (display.rs:48-49,
    general_purpose/mod.rs:69).
  
  Functional correctness (concern #4):
  - Length math uses checked_add/checked_mul where overflow is possible
    (encode.rs:86-87, encode.rs:104, engine/mod.rs:121,208,316).
    encoded_len() returns Option to surface usize overflow.
  - decode_helper indexing: complete_quads_len enforces output_len >=
    quads/4*3 before the unrolled chunk loop; decode_suffix uses
    get_mut with OutputSliceTooSmall fallback for the final 0-3 bytes.
  - Padding handling in decode_suffix.rs:31-109 covers all four
    documented bad-padding cases plus DecodePaddingMode variants and
    trailing-bits canonicalness via mask check at line 133-141.
  - read::DecoderReader carefully tracks input_consumed_len offsets so
    error positions remain accurate across the BUF_SIZE-bounded internal
    buffer; padding-after-padding reported at first pad offset.
  - write::EncoderWriter rolls back extra_input_occupied_len on writer
    error and avoids reentrancy via the `panicked` flag in Drop.
  - The fast encode loop reads u64s with 2 bytes of headroom
    (`last_fast_index = len.saturating_sub(BLOCKS_PER_FAST_LOOP*6+2)`)
    so the final u64 read never goes OOB.
  
  Advisories:
  - RUSTSEC-2017-0004 (integer overflow in encode_config_buf) affects
    only very old pre-0.5 versions. 0.22.1 uses checked arithmetic and
    is not affected.
  
  CI runs cargo test on stable/beta/nightly plus MSRV, no_std target
  thumbv6m-none-eabi, clippy on stable, and cargo-fuzz on nightly.
  No miri needed (no unsafe).
