comment: |-
  Tiny crate (~540 lines lib.rs + ~210 lines test.rs) providing checked
  numeric cast functions for primitive types. Authored by japaric, MIT/
  Apache-2.0 dual licensed, repo at github.com/japaric/cast.rs.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious/suspicious): clean. No build.rs, no proc-macros,
  no I/O, no runtime dependencies (only quickcheck as dev-dep). Cargo
  manifest is vanilla.
  
  Concern #2 (unsafe w/o SAFETY): N/A. lib.rs:94 has
  `#![deny(unsafe_code)]`. Grep across the source confirms zero `unsafe`
  occurrences (CHANGELOG notes #41 removed the last internal unsafe).
  
  Concern #3 (unsafe w/o miri): N/A - no unsafe.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): the float-to-integer logic in `from_float!`
  (lib.rs:267) is the only non-trivial piece. It correctly handles the
  "MAX rounds up" case for lossy conversions (e.g. u32::MAX as f32 ->
  2^32) by subtracting 1 ULP from the computed max before comparing,
  using `dst_bits < MANTISSA_DIGITS` to detect lossless cases. The
  f32->u128 path uses `from_float_dst!` which skips the overflow check;
  this is sound because the largest finite f32 ((2 - 2^-23) * 2^127) is
  strictly less than 2^128, so every finite f32 fits in u128. Tests in
  src/test.rs cover NaN, infinity, gh16 (negative-near-zero truncation),
  gh15 (large-exponent overflow), and gh23 (lossless integer MAX
  representation). MSRV is documented as 1.31 with `#![deny(warnings)]`,
  which is brittle but affects only the crate's own build.
  
  Lints used: `#![allow(const_err)]` to silence macro-generated
  comparison warnings - acceptable.
