  severity: medium
  comment: |
    `StreamCipherCore::try_apply_keystream_partial` at
    `src/stream_core.rs:108-112` computes
    `blocks = buf.len() % BlockSize::USIZE` (and `+ 1` on the
    non-divisible branch) where it must compute
    `blocks = buf.len() / BlockSize::USIZE`. The "remaining keystream
    sufficient?" precondition is therefore not enforced; the function
    proceeds to drive the backend past `remaining_blocks()`.
    Reproduction: repros/cipher/0.4.4/try-apply-keystream-partial-uses-mod-instead-of-div/
- id: unsafe-without-safety-comment-stream-core-into-chunks
  severity: low
  comment: |
    `into_chunks` at `src/stream_core.rs:198-212` contains an `unsafe`
    block (two `slice::from_raw_parts_mut` calls and one `ptr.add`)
    with no `// SAFETY:` comment. The invariants are knowable from the
    surrounding arithmetic, but they aren't documented at the call
    site. Caps this review at `neutral` per the project rubric.
comment: |-
  Pure-trait crate (~1400 lines across 8 files, with the bulk in `block.rs`
  and the dev-feature test macros). No `build.rs`, no proc-macros, no FFI,
  no network or filesystem I/O, no `std::process`. The only `include_bytes!`
  calls are inside `#[macro_export]`ed test helpers gated on the `dev`
  feature and are interpolated by the downstream test crate, not the
  trait crate itself. Dependencies are all `RustCrypto` siblings
  (`crypto-common`, `inout`, optional `blobby`, optional `zeroize`).
  Licensing and metadata match the rest of the RustCrypto ecosystem.
  
  Two `unsafe` occurrences:
   - `src/stream_wrapper.rs:55-56` — `core::hint::unreachable_unchecked()`
     with a `// SAFETY:` comment whose stated invariant ("pos is set only
     to values smaller than block size") is upheld by `set_pos_unchecked`'s
     debug_assert and the internal call sites I traced.
   - `src/stream_core.rs:206-211` — `slice::from_raw_parts_mut` (called
     twice, plus `ptr.add(tail_pos)`) inside the private `into_chunks`
     helper, with NO `// SAFETY:` comment. The invariants
     (`tail_pos = N::USIZE * chunks_len <= buf.len()`, lifetimes tied to
     `&mut [T]` input, alignment of `*mut GenericArray<T, N>` matching
     `*mut T`) are knowable but the author left them undocumented.
     Per AGENTS.md rule #2 this caps the rating at `neutral`.
  
  No `miri` invocation in any visible CI config (the crate ships only
  `Cargo.toml` + `LICENSE-*` + `CHANGELOG.md` + sources; the workspace
  CI lives in the upstream `RustCrypto/traits` monorepo, not in the
  published artifact). The `into_chunks` block is miri-testable in
  principle.
  
  Found one functional-correctness bug in
  `StreamCipherCore::try_apply_keystream_partial`
  (`src/stream_core.rs:108-112`): the block-count expression uses `%`
  where it must use `/`, so the "is the remaining keystream sufficient"
  check is bypassed for any input whose length is an exact multiple of
  the block size, and under-counts by `buf.len() / bs` blocks in general.
  The default method silently drives the backend past
  `remaining_blocks()`, which in concrete stream ciphers either panics
  or — if the backend wraps — produces a reused keystream. Note that
  `StreamCipherCoreWrapper::check_remaining` in `stream_wrapper.rs:96-100`
  computes the same quantity correctly, so the bug is localised to the
  default-method path.
  
  Reproduction: `repros/cipher/0.4.4/try-apply-keystream-partial-uses-mod-instead-of-div/`.
