  - Only `std::process::exit` call is `Error::exit` in error/mod.rs:248,
    the documented "print error then exit" helper. Only env access is
    `env::args_os` for CLI parsing (command.rs:664/688/728) and `env::var_os`
    for the documented `Arg::env(name)` feature (arg.rs:2207) plus
    COLUMNS/LINES for help wrapping (help_template.rs:1123). The `unsafe`
    occurrences in grep are entirely inside doctest snippets calling
    `env::set_var` (Rust 2024 edition requires unsafe there).
