  Concern #4 (correctness): no reproducible bugs found on this pass. Notable
  spots that read carefully:
  - parser/parser.rs:1291 counts occurrences with `saturating_add(1)` --
    correctly avoids overflow on ArgAction::Count.
  - builder/range.rs From<RangeTo<usize>>/From<Range<usize>> use
    `saturating_sub(1)` to convert exclusive to inclusive end; the
    `..0` edge case produces `0..=0` (i.e. "no values"), surprising but
    not exploitable.
  - builder/value_parser.rs RangedI64/U64ValueParser parse i64/u64 first,
    then bounds-check, then `try_into` the target -- correct order.
  - output/textwrap/core.rs `display_width` enters control-sequence mode on
    any ASCII control char and exits only on `m`; a bare control char in
    user-supplied help text (without a following `m`) would let subsequent
    text be counted as width 0. Cosmetic, not a memory or panic issue.
