  Maintained by clap-rs (long-established CLI parsing project; clap_lex
  is the tokenizer extracted from the main clap crate). Read every .rs
  file under src/ (lib.rs, ext.rs) and Cargo.toml. The crate is small
  (~520 lines lib.rs, ~285 lines ext.rs).
  
  Concern #1 (malicious/suspicious): no build.rs (`build = false` in
  Cargo.toml line 17), no proc-macro, no `include_bytes!`, no
  `std::process::Command`, no network or libc, no obfuscation. The
  only `include_*!` is `include_str!("../README.md")` for doctest
  scaffolding (lib.rs:524, gated on `cfg(doctest)`). Dependencies are
  empty at runtime; `automod` 1.0.16 (dtolnay) is the sole dev-dep.
  License is dual MIT/Apache-2.0, repository points to clap-rs/clap,
  include list (Cargo.toml lines 18-25) is narrow.
  
  Concern #2 (unsafe + SAFETY): five `unsafe` sites, all in support of
  `OsStr::from_encoded_bytes_unchecked` and the `pub(crate) unsafe fn
  split_at` helper. Every site has a SAFETY (or `# Safety`) comment
  stating the UTF-8-boundary invariant: ext.rs:204-206 (strip_prefix),
  ext.rs:229-231 (split_once), ext.rs:272-274 (split_at doc-comment
  precondition), lib.rs:457 (next_value_os, index from char_indices),
  lib.rs:483-484 (split_nonutf8_once, valid_up_to from str::from_utf8).
  All invariants check out; valid UTF-8 boundaries are also valid
  WTF-8 boundaries (Windows OsStr encoding), so the from_encoded_
  bytes_unchecked contract is satisfied on both platforms.
  
  Concern #3 (miri): unsafe is miri-testable but upstream CI does not
  run miri (see issues block). Cap rating at `positive`.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): walked through `is_number` for edge cases
  ("", ".", "1.e2", "1e", "1e2e3"); behavior matches the documented
  intent. `find` / `split_once` rely on the fact that a valid-UTF-8
  needle can only match at WTF-8 boundaries within an OsStr —
  verified by reasoning about which UTF-8 lead bytes coincide with
  WTF-8 surrogate bytes. `RawArgs::seek` casts usize<->i64<->u64; no
  overflow on 64-bit targets given Vec length bounds. No bugs
  reproducible enough to warrant a repro.
