package:
  source: https://crates.io
  name: crossbeam-channel
  version: 0.5.15
  revision: d35ffde18a76ae9667f602d8c0127ff89ac2e4d4
  digest: BOhBSPqK9jvJQNcAeAhxJdjdya3TZRPf0PinqfRABAA
review:
  thoroughness: high
  understanding: medium
  rating: neutral
advisories:
- ids:
  - RUSTSEC-2025-0024
  severity: high
  range: minor
  comment: |
    Double-free on Drop in unbounded channels (`flavors/list.rs`),
    regression introduced in 0.5.12 by the memory-leak fix MR #1084 and
    fixed in 0.5.15 by MR #1187. Affects 0.5.12-0.5.14, which are all
    yanked. 0.5.15 (this review) is the fixed release; the `range: minor`
    indicates earlier patch releases of the same 0.5.x line are affected.
comment: |-
  MPMC channel library from the official crossbeam-rs project. Read every
  .rs file in src/ (channel.rs, counter.rs, context.rs, err.rs, select.rs,
  select_macro.rs, utils.rs, waker.rs, and all six flavors). No build.rs,
  no proc-macros, no_std-capable, dual MIT/Apache-2.0, single std-only
  dependency on crossbeam-utils.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious): nothing found. The code is intricate lock-free
  concurrency (Vyukov bounded MPMC in flavors/array.rs, linked-list of
  32-slot blocks in flavors/list.rs, mutex-guarded rendezvous in
  flavors/zero.rs, atomic-deadline in flavors/at.rs and flavors/tick.rs)
  but every unsafe operation is local to channel internals -- no I/O, no
  syscalls, no FFI, no obfuscated data.
  
  Concern #2 (SAFETY comments): many unsafe blocks lack formal `// SAFETY:`
  comments. flavors/list.rs:86-99 (Block::new) does it right with explicit
  invariants for zero-initialization. Counter-examples include counter.rs:45
  / counter.rs:100 (`unsafe { &*self.counter }`), the `unsafe fn release`
  on counter.rs:67/122, the transmute_copy chain in channel.rs:766-833 and
  channel.rs:1517-1522 that relies on T == Instant for the At/Tick flavors,
  the Drop unsafe blocks in channel.rs:657 and channel.rs:1152, the
  pub(crate) `unsafe fn write/read` on the flavors that have no /// # Safety
  doc, the get_unchecked + ptr cast pattern throughout flavors/array.rs and
  flavors/list.rs, and the lifetime-erasing transmute in select_macro.rs:756
  /778/808/850/882 (these have an explanatory `// Erase the lifetime ...`
  but not a formal SAFETY annotation). Per project rubric this caps the
  rating at `neutral`.
  
  Concern #3 (miri): the upstream CI (.github/workflows/ci.yml in the
  crossbeam-channel-0.5.15 tag) runs `cargo miri test -p crossbeam-channel`
  with `-Zmiri-symbolic-alignment-check -Zmiri-disable-isolation
  -Zmiri-ignore-leaks`, plus cargo-careful and a randomize-layout RUSTFLAGS
  matrix. Pure-Rust unsafe is therefore exercised under miri. No cap from
  this concern.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): 0.5.15 is the release that fixes
  RUSTSEC-2025-0024 (double-free on Drop introduced in 0.5.12, see #1187).
  The fix is visible in flavors/list.rs:584-646 -- `discard_all_messages`
  now uses `self.head.block.swap(ptr::null_mut(), AcqRel)` at both load
  sites (lines 604 and 614), so Drop can no longer race with discard on
  the same block pointer. 0.5.12-0.5.14 are yanked. No further bugs found
  on inspection. Spot-checked the integer/index arithmetic in array.rs
  (`one_lap = next_power_of_two(cap+1) * 2`, head/tail stamp packing) and
  list.rs (block-of-32 indexing with SHIFT/MARK_BIT/LAP); the wrap-around
  uses `wrapping_add`/`wrapping_sub` consistently.
  
  Net: rating `neutral` because of the SAFETY-comment gap, not because of
  any concrete defect.
