package:
  source: https://crates.io
  name: crossbeam-epoch
  version: 0.9.18
  revision: 9c3182abebb36bdc9446d75d4644190fef70fa01
  digest: KmvGTQIId6zAyUCjdIMyiJbKayjbBfJSb5F56Xgu4sA
review:
  thoroughness: medium
  understanding: medium
  rating: neutral
comment: |-
  Epoch-based GC primitive from the crossbeam project; foundational concurrency
  crate (170M+ downloads). Read every .rs in src/ (atomic.rs, collector.rs,
  default.rs, deferred.rs, epoch.rs, guard.rs, internal.rs, sync/{list,queue,
  once_lock,mod}.rs), plus tests/loom.rs and examples/sanitize.rs.
  
  Supply chain (concern #1): No build.rs, no proc-macro, no include_bytes!, no
  network/process/filesystem I/O, no obfuscation. Sole runtime dep is
  crossbeam-utils (sibling crate, same maintainers); loom is an optional
  cfg-gated test dep. License MIT/Apache-2.0, repo on github.com/crossbeam-rs.
  
  Unsafe with SAFETY comments (concern #2): heavy unsafe usage (~188 unsafe
  tokens across src/), but only a handful of `// SAFETY:` annotations. The
  pattern is older: unsafe fn definitions document invariants in `/// # Safety`
  doc sections (e.g. atomic.rs:160-191 for Pointable, atomic.rs:1037-1039 for
  Pointer::from_usize), and unsafe blocks rely on those documented contracts
  rather than restating them inline. Per the rubric this caps the rating at
  neutral; the unsafe itself is well-trodden lock-free code (Michael-Scott
  queue, intrusive list, Treiber-style epoch tracking) that has been used in
  production for years and survived extensive miri/loom scrutiny.
  
  Unsafe with miri (concern #3): the crate has pervasive `#[cfg(miri)]` test
  knobs (collector.rs, queue.rs, internal.rs reduces MAX_OBJECTS to 4 under
  miri). The parent repo's ci/miri.sh runs `cargo miri test -p crossbeam-epoch`
  with `-Zmiri-symbolic-alignment-check -Zmiri-disable-stacked-borrows
  -Zmiri-ignore-leaks`. Stacked borrows is disabled (crossbeam-rs/crossbeam#545)
  so aliasing bugs would not be caught, but core UB checks still run. ci.yml
  also runs a separate loom job (ci/crossbeam-epoch-loom.sh) covering tests/
  loom.rs. No miri penalty applied.
  
  Correctness (concern #4): no reproducible bugs found. Notable observations:
  Local::unpin (internal.rs:444) does `guard_count - 1` without an overflow
  guard but is invariant-protected by Guard::drop; pin uses checked_add. The
  x86 SeqCst-via-cmpxchg hack in Local::pin (internal.rs:394-422) is annotated
  as experimentally validated rather than formally proven. Owned::Drop calls
  T::drop on the raw pointer with only a debug_assert against zero in
  Owned::from_usize. Array::layout panics on overflow via unwrap, consistent
  with stdlib behavior.
  
  No RUSTSEC advisories listed for this crate. Rating capped at neutral solely
  due to the missing `// SAFETY:` annotations per the project rubric.
