  (used transitively by ~all Rust concurrency code). Read every .rs file
  in src/ (lib.rs, backoff.rs, cache_padded.rs, thread.rs, atomic/{mod,
  atomic_cell,consume,seq_lock,seq_lock_wide}.rs, sync/{mod,once_lock,
  parker,sharded_lock,wait_group}.rs), plus Cargo.toml, build.rs,
  build-common.rs, no_atomic.rs, README, CHANGELOG, and the CI workflow.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious/suspicious): build.rs only consumes TARGET and
  CARGO_CFG_SANITIZE env vars and emits cargo:rustc-cfg / rustc-check-cfg
  / warning directives plus rerun-if-changed for no_atomic.rs. No network,
  no FS access outside cargo's output channel, no shelling out. The
  included no_atomic.rs is a 4-entry constant array of target triples.
  No proc-macro, no include_bytes!, no Command, no obfuscation. Runtime
  deps: zero in default config; optional loom 0.7.1 gated on
  cfg(crossbeam_loom) for testing only. Dev-dep rand 0.8. License
  MIT/Apache-2.0, repository on github.com/crossbeam-rs.
  
  Concern #2 (unsafe + SAFETY): heavy unsafe usage. Counted ~70 unsafe
  tokens across the crate. Coverage is partial. SAFETY-annotated:
  atomic_cell.rs:86-92 (into_inner), 310-316 (Drop::drop), once_lock.rs
  :50-51, 55-56, 84-85; rustdoc `# Safety` sections on once_lock.rs
  get_unchecked, parker.rs Parker/Unparker::from_raw. Without SAFETY
  prefix: every atomic_cell.rs `unsafe { atomic_load/store/swap/cae(...) }`
  call site (lines 143, 163, 215, 267), all impl_arithmetic!-generated
  `unsafe { &mut *(self.as_ptr()) }` and `unsafe { &*(self.as_ptr() as
  *const atomic::$atomic) }` blocks (40+ occurrences), the four
  `unsafe fn atomic_*` private helpers (lines 1048, 1090, 1109, 1133)
  which have no `# Safety` docs, sharded_lock.rs lifetime-transmute and
  UnsafeCell-cast blocks (lines 193, 349, 359, 424, 498, 529, 556, 562),
  thread.rs:466 `mem::transmute` erasing `'env` bound (has narrative
  rationale but not the canonical prefix). The `unsafe impl Send/Sync`
  markers (parker.rs:58/221/222, sharded_lock.rs:86/87/492/523,
  cache_padded.rs:152/153, thread.rs:224/489/490, atomic_cell.rs:47/48,
  once_lock.rs:16/17) carry no rationale comments. Per rubric §2 this
  caps rating at `neutral`. The underlying invariants ARE correct — this
  code has years of production exposure and miri runs in CI — but the
  annotation discipline is below the rubric bar.
  
  Concern #3 (miri): upstream CI (.github/workflows/ci.yml on the
  crossbeam-utils-0.8.21 tag) runs ci/miri.sh with `cargo miri test -p
  crossbeam-utils` under MIRIFLAGS=-Zmiri-symbolic-alignment-check
  -Zmiri-disable-isolation, plus a cargo-careful job and a randomize-
  layout RUSTFLAGS env. Pure-Rust unsafe is exercised. No additional
  cap.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): no reproducible bugs found. Spot-checks:
  AtomicCell's lock-shard array uses LEN=67 (prime, deliberate per the
  in-source comment to avoid alignment-induced bias); seq_lock_wide.rs
  acknowledges the rare double-wrap window it cannot detect; Parker's
  state machine is the textbook std::thread::park pattern (EMPTY/PARKED/
  NOTIFIED with a coordinated swap and a panic on inconsistent state at
  parker.rs:351/372); ShardedLock holds 8 RwLock shards selected by
  current_index() & 7 (NUM_SHARDS is power-of-two as asserted); write
  path locks all shards in order, drops them in reverse; WaitGroup uses
  Mutex<usize> + Condvar with count starting at 1, decrement in Drop,
  notify_all on reaching zero — race-free. The arithmetic in
  impl_arithmetic! fallbacks uses wrapping_add/sub deliberately. The
  scope() implementation in thread.rs promotes any unwinding panic to
  an abort via AbortOnPanic to prevent dangling references escaping
  the scope. Note that crossbeam-utils thread::scope is soft-deprecated
  in favor of std::thread::scope (Rust 1.63+) per its own docstring.
  
  Rating capped at `neutral` solely due to the missing `// SAFETY:`
  annotations per the project rubric; functional code quality is high
  and consistent with the rest of the crossbeam-rs ecosystem.
