comment: |-
  Implementation crate behind the `darling` proc-macro framework. This crate
  is the heavy lifter: it defines the FromMeta/FromDeriveInput/FromField/etc.
  traits, their impls for std and `syn` types, the error/Accumulator machinery,
  the `usage` module for generic-parameter tracing, and the codegen module
  that emits the trait impls used by `darling_macro`.
  
  Read every .rs file under src/ (~10.3 kLOC), Cargo.toml, and the original
  Cargo.toml.orig.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious / suspicious code): nothing flagged. Cargo.toml has
  `build = false`, no build.rs exists, and `proc-macro = true` is NOT set —
  this is a plain library, not a proc-macro. Grep across src/ found no
  `include_bytes!`, no `std::process`, no network APIs, no `std::fs`, no
  `libc::`, no `asm!`, no `#[no_mangle]`. The lone occurrence of the word
  "unsafe" is a string literal in error/mod.rs:210 mapping `Expr::Unsafe` to
  the diagnostic string "unsafe". Dependencies are the standard proc-macro
  stack (proc-macro2, quote, syn, fnv, ident_case) with optional serde and
  strsim; license MIT, repository github.com/TedDriggs/darling (long-standing
  upstream).
  
  Concerns #2 and #3 (unsafe / miri): N/A — zero `unsafe` blocks or `unsafe fn`
  in this crate.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness bugs): the codegen layer panics in several places
  (e.g. codegen/from_meta_impl.rs:77 "Multi-field tuples are not supported",
  codegen/trait_impl.rs:141 "Core loop on enums isn't supported", and similar
  in variant.rs / variant_data.rs). These all fire at proc-macro expansion
  time when a downstream derive misuses darling, surfacing as a compile-time
  panic rather than a graceful Error. Suboptimal UX but not a soundness or
  runtime concern. The usage/type_params.rs and usage/lifetimes.rs files also
  panic on currently-unknown syn enum variants ("Unknown syn::Type", etc.);
  the comments acknowledge this as a TODO to convert to fallible returns.
  Data::empty_from panics on Unions, but Data::try_empty_from provides the
  fallible alternative. The `Accumulator` Drop impl deliberately panics if
  unfinished — this is documented drop-bomb behavior, not a bug.
  
  Crate is widely used (foundation of the darling family — millions of
  downloads/month) and maintained by Ted Driggs, who has shipped this crate
  for years. The companion darling and darling_macro 0.21.3 reviews are
  already in this repo; this completes the trio.
  
  No issues warranting an `issues:` block. Comfortable depending on this.
