comment: |-
  Tiny proc-macro façade for the darling family (41 LOC). src/lib.rs
  declares seven `#[proc_macro_derive]` entry points (FromMeta,
  FromMetaItem, FromAttributes, FromDeriveInput, FromField,
  FromTypeParam, FromVariant). Each is a one-liner that runs
  `parse_macro_input!` then delegates to the corresponding
  `darling_core::derive::*` function. FromMetaItem (line 11) is a
  deprecation stub that emits a compile error pointing at FromMeta.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious / suspicious): no build.rs, no `unsafe`,
  no `include_bytes!`/`include_str!`, no `std::process`, no network
  or filesystem APIs, no env reads. Grep across the tree returned
  zero hits for any of those patterns. Dependencies are `darling_core`
  (pinned `=0.21.3`, sibling crate by same author, separately reviewed),
  `quote 1.0.18`, and `syn 2.0.15` — all standard, widely audited.
