comment: |-
  Façade crate that re-exports the proc-macros from `derive_more-impl =2.1.1`
  and provides supporting trait/error types used by the generated code.
  All proc-macro logic lives in `derive_more-impl` and is out of scope here;
  that crate needs its own review.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious/suspicious): nothing flagged.
  - No `build.rs` (`build = false` in Cargo.toml).
  - `proc-macro = true` is not set; this is a normal library crate.
  - No `include_bytes!`, `std::process`, network/socket APIs, or `libc`
    references anywhere under `src/`.
  - Single non-dev dependency is `derive_more-impl =2.1.1` (same author,
    exact-version pin). Optional `rustc_version` is gated behind the
    `testing-helpers` feature only.
  - License MIT, repository link present, author matches the long-standing
    maintainer (Jelte Fennema).
  
  Concern #2/#3 (unsafe): non-applicable. `src/lib.rs:49` has
  `#![forbid(non_ascii_idents, unsafe_code)]`. The only matches for
  `unsafe` under `src/` are this forbid attribute. No SAFETY caps apply.
  
  Concern #4 (functional correctness): read every file under `src/`
  (`lib.rs`, `add.rs`, `as.rs`, `as_dyn_error.rs`, `cmp.rs`, `convert.rs`,
  `fmt.rs`, `ops.rs`, `str.rs`, `try_unwrap.rs`) plus `examples/`. The
  helper types are small wrappers over `&'static str` formatted into
  `Display`/`Error` impls; no arithmetic, indexing, or input parsing in
  this crate. The `DebugTuple`/`Padded` writer in `fmt.rs` is a faithful
  reimplementation of `core::fmt::DebugTuple` with an added
  `finish_non_exhaustive`. `as.rs` is the standard autoref-based
  specialization trick. Nothing bug-shaped found.
